{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/codeedittextview.CodeEditTextView\/documentation\/CodeEditTextView","doc:\/\/codeedittextview.CodeEditTextView\/documentation\/CodeEditTextView\/TextLayoutManager"]]},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Lays out all visible lines"}],"kind":"symbol","sections":[],"metadata":{"externalID":"s:16CodeEditTextView0C13LayoutManagerC11layoutLines2inShy10Foundation4UUIDVGSo6CGRectVSg_tF","role":"symbol","modules":[{"name":"CodeEditTextView"}],"roleHeading":"Instance Method","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"layoutLines","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"in","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@NSRect","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"NSRect"},{"kind":"text","text":"?) -> "},{"text":"Set","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sh"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"text":"TextLine","preciseIdentifier":"s:16CodeEditTextView0C4LineC","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":".","kind":"text"},{"text":"ID","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:16CodeEditTextView0C4LineC2IDa"},{"kind":"text","text":">"}],"extendedModule":"CodeEditTextView","title":"layoutLines(in:)","symbolKind":"method"},"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/codeedittextview\/textlayoutmanager\/layoutlines(in:)"]}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"@discardableResult","kind":"attribute"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"layoutLines","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"text":"in","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"rect","kind":"internalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@NSRect","text":"NSRect"},{"text":"? = nil) -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Set","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sh"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/codeedittextview.CodeEditTextView\/documentation\/CodeEditTextView\/TextLine","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"TextLine","preciseIdentifier":"s:16CodeEditTextView0C4LineC"},{"kind":"text","text":"."},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:16CodeEditTextView0C4LineC2IDa","text":"ID","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":">","kind":"text"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Overview Of The Layout Routine","level":2,"anchor":"Overview-Of-The-Layout-Routine","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The basic premise of this method is that it loops over all lines in the given rect (defaults to the visible"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"rect), checks if the line needs a layout calculation, and performs layout on the line if it does."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The thing that makes this layout method so fast is the second point, checking if a line needs layout. To"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"determine if a line needs a layout pass, the layout manager can check three things:","type":"text"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"1","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":" Was the line laid out under the assumption of a different maximum layout width?"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"For instance, if a line was previously broken by the line wrapping setting, it won’t need to wrap once the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"line wrapping is disabled. This will detect that, and cause the lines to be recalculated.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"2","type":"text"}]},{"text":" Was the line previously not visible? This is determined by keeping a set of visible line IDs. If the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"line does not appear in that set, we can assume it was previously off screen and may need layout."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"3"}]},{"type":"text","text":" Was the line entirely laid out? We break up lines into line fragments. When we do layout, we determine"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"all line fragments but don’t necessarily place them all in the view. This checks if all line fragments have"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"been placed in the view. If not, we need to place them."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Once it has been determined that a line needs layout, we perform layout by recalculating it’s line fragments,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"removing all old line fragment views, and creating new ones for the line."}]},{"text":"Laziness","level":2,"anchor":"Laziness","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"At the end of the layout pass, we clean up any old lines by updating the set of visible line IDs and fragment","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"IDs. Any IDs that no longer appear in those sets are removed to save resources. This facilitates the text view’s"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"ability to only render text that is visible and saves tons of resources (similar to the lazy loading of"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"collection or table views).","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The other important lazy attribute is the line iteration. Line iteration is done lazily. As we iterate","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"through lines and potentially update their heights, the next line is only queried for ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"after"}]},{"text":" the updates are","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"finished."}]},{"anchor":"Reentry","level":2,"text":"Reentry","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"An important thing to note is that this method cannot be reentered. If a layout pass has begun while a layout","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"pass is already ongoing, internal data structures will be broken. In debug builds, this is checked with a simple","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"boolean and assertion."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"To help ensure this property, all view modifications are performed within a ","type":"text"},{"code":"CATransaction","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". This guarantees","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"that macOS calls "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"layout"},{"text":" on any related views only after we’ve finished inserting and removing line fragment","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"views. Otherwise, inserting a line fragment view could trigger a layout pass prematurely and cause this method","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to re-enter."}]},{"name":"Warning","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This is probably not what you’re looking for. If you need to invalidate layout, or update lines, this"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"is not the way to do so. This should only be called when macOS performs layout.","type":"text"}]}],"style":"warning","type":"aside"}]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/codeedittextview.CodeEditTextView\/documentation\/CodeEditTextView\/TextLayoutManager\/layoutLines(in:)","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"references":{"doc://codeedittextview.CodeEditTextView/documentation/CodeEditTextView":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/codeedittextview.CodeEditTextView\/documentation\/CodeEditTextView","abstract":[{"text":"A text editor designed to edit code documents.","type":"text"}],"url":"\/documentation\/codeedittextview","type":"topic","kind":"symbol","title":"CodeEditTextView","role":"collection"},"doc://codeedittextview.CodeEditTextView/documentation/CodeEditTextView/TextLine":{"title":"TextLine","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"TextLine","kind":"identifier"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/codeedittextview.CodeEditTextView\/documentation\/CodeEditTextView\/TextLine","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/codeedittextview\/textline","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"TextLine"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Represents a displayable line of text."}],"kind":"symbol"},"doc://codeedittextview.CodeEditTextView/documentation/CodeEditTextView/TextLayoutManager/layoutLines(in:)":{"abstract":[{"text":"Lays out all visible lines","type":"text"}],"type":"topic","kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/codeedittextview\/textlayoutmanager\/layoutlines(in:)","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"layoutLines","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"in","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"NSRect","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@NSRect"},{"text":"?) -> ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sh","text":"Set"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"text":"TextLine","preciseIdentifier":"s:16CodeEditTextView0C4LineC","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"."},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:16CodeEditTextView0C4LineC2IDa","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"ID"},{"text":">","kind":"text"}],"title":"layoutLines(in:)","identifier":"doc:\/\/codeedittextview.CodeEditTextView\/documentation\/CodeEditTextView\/TextLayoutManager\/layoutLines(in:)","role":"symbol"},"doc://codeedittextview.CodeEditTextView/documentation/CodeEditTextView/TextLayoutManager":{"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"TextLayoutManager","kind":"identifier"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The text layout manager manages laying out lines in a code document."}],"kind":"symbol","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/codeedittextview.CodeEditTextView\/documentation\/CodeEditTextView\/TextLayoutManager","title":"TextLayoutManager","role":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/codeedittextview\/textlayoutmanager","fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"TextLayoutManager","kind":"identifier"}]}}}